article.headline: Wis.-Milwaukee 63, Ill.-Chicago 62
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Deion James hit a 3-pointer with a second left on the clock to give Wisconsin-Milwaukee a 63-62 victory over Illinois-Chicago on Saturday. The Panthers (14-8, 9-3 Horizon League) trailed by 10 with 1:27 left in the game, but went on a 9-1 run on a pair of 3-pointers from Tone Boyle and another 3 by Tony Meier to cut the Flames' lead to two with 43 seconds left. Boyle missed a potential game-tying jumper with eight seconds left, but James came back to hit the game-winning shot. Boyle and Meier scored 17 points each to lead the Panthers, who trailed 35-21 at halftime. Tori Boyd scored 23 to lead the Flames (10-11, 3-8), who lost at Wisconsin-Green Bay on Wednesday.
